[ctns_make id='gen_linear_func_x_intercept_and_y_intercept_linear_function']

  [ctns_front style='']
X-Intercept and Y-Intercept<br/>Linear Function
  [/ctns_front]  

  [ctns_back style='width:80%;font-size:90%;']
The $$y$$-intercept of a function is the value of $$y$$ when $$x=0$$. The $$x$$-intercept of a function is the value of $$x$$ when $$y=0$$.
  [/ctns_back]  

  [ctns_frontspeak]
X-Intercept and Y-Intercept -- Linear Function
  [/ctns_frontspeak]  

  [ctns_backspeak]
The y-intercept of a function is the value of y when x equals zero. -- The x-intercept of a function is the value of x when why equals zero..
  [/ctns_backspeak]  

[/ctns_make]
